<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-44-1301 </DOCNO><TEXT>A method is developed for determining energy expenditures on viscoplasticdeformation in the rapid dispersion of a silicate melt into a fibrousmass under nonisothermal conditions. It is shown that the energy expendedon overcoming internal friction during fiber formation is twice as greatas the energy needed to overcome surface forces. Experimental and theoreticalvalues of the specific surface energy of a fibrous mass are comparedfor different types of fibers.</TEXT></DOC>